issue.title: Run time error: Parameter name cannot be empty and must be a string.

repository.name: sklearn-onnx
repository.description: Convert scikit-learn models and pipelines to ONNX

issue.body:
I am trying to convert sklearn pipeline to onnx and end up getting runtime error. The code looks like this:

`update_registered_converter(XGBClassifier, 'XGBClassifier', calculate_xgboost_classifier_output_shapes, convert_xgboost)`  


`pipeline = Pipeline(steps=[
    ('preprocessor' , preprocessor),
    ('classifier', xgb_model)
])
`


`pipeline.fit(X_train_down, y_train_down, 
             **params_fit)`


`model_onnx = convert_sklearn(pipeline, name='pipeline_xgb', initial_types=inputs)`

The error stacktrace:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3057235/65150573-b2813200-da24-11e9-9deb-2dc46a98aded.png)


Even though I have passed parameter _name="pipeline_xgb"_ I am getting runtime error.

body:
Hello @francaru ,

I am facing the same issue when I try to convert the xgboost classifier in a pipeline. Were you able to solve this or waiting for the support?

Hi @varshakirani,

Unfortunately no I wasn't able to solve the issue. Still waiting for the support team to apply the fix.
I'm adding unit tests to cover that scenario in sklearn-onnx. See https://github.com/onnx/sklearn-onnx/pull/262. Once this PR is merged, this issue will be fixed.

I have created a pull request, repairing the missing name arguments mentioned by @francaru 
https://github.com/onnx/onnxmltools/pull/337
Thanks, you need to sign the CLA if you want us to merge it. The current master branch of skl2onnx also includes a modification not to raise an exception in that case.

> Thanks, you need to sign the CLA if you want us to merge it. The current master branch of skl2onnx also includes a modification not to raise an exception in that case.

I have signed the CLA, but it still shows "CLA not signed yet"
Can we close this issue since PR #337 has been merged?

I can confirm that this issue has been resolved. Thank you for your help.

Kind regards
